Class ERxPatientData

java.lang.Object
ca.openosp.openo.rx.erx.model.ERxPatientData
public class ERxPatientData extends Object
A value type that stores the patient data accepted by the External Prescriber.

      Creates an instance of a ERxPatientData. This constructor only fills the mandatory fields.

    • ERxPatientData

      public ERxPatientData(String patientId, String firstname, String lastname, String chartNumber, String pin1, int pin1type, String pin1Expiration, int hip)
      Creates an instance of a ERxPatientData. This constructor only fills the mandatory fields and strongly recommended fields.
      Parameters:
      patientId - The unique patient identifier provided by the client [OSCAR] software.
      firstname - The patient's first given name.
      lastname - The patient's surname.
      chartNumber - The patient's chart number.
      pin1 - The patient's primary identification number.
      pin1type - The type of primary identification number.
      pin1Expiration - The date that the primary identification number expires in free-form text.
      hip - The patient's public Health Insurance Plan identifier.
